address: M87G+453, San Juan, La Union
description: A spacious restaurant offering Filipino comfort dishes like pinakbet, kaldereta, and grilled tuna, complemented by signature cocktails and local craft beers.ÃÂ

address: M85C+WX3, 183 2, 183 MacArthur Hwy, San Juan, La Union
description: Known for its wood-fired pizzas, seafood pasta, and grilled pork belly, Kermit provides a laid-back atmosphere with both indoor and outdoor seating.ÃÂ

address: 229 Urbiztondo Rd, San Juan, La Union
description: Specializes in Filipino rice bowls topped with favorites like tapa, pares, and chicken adobo flakes, offering a taste of local flavors.ÃÂ

address: Urbiztondo Beach Urbiztondo, San Juan, 2514 La Union
description: Offers Greek cuisine with dishes such as lamb souvlaki, lamb chops, and kebab rice meals, providing a taste of Greece in La Union.

address: M84C+HG2, Brgy. Urbiztondo, Manila, North Road, San Juan, La Union
description: A popular spot for burgers, known for its juicy and flavorful offerings, making it a must-visit for burger enthusiasts.

address: San Juan, 2514 La Union
description: Situated by the sea, Fatwave serves dishes like grilled mahi-mahi, sinigang na hipon, and adobong pusit, emphasizing fresh seafood.

address: M85C+VVW, MacArthur National Highway, San Juan, La Union
description: A hip cafÃÂ© known for its farm-to-cup coffee made from high-grade specialty beans, paired with sweet treats like their signature Indoor SÃÂmores.

address: 5 Biday Bridge, San Fernando, 2500 La Union
description: A buffet-style restaurant offering a wide variety of Filipino, Asian, and international dishes, perfect for large gatherings and celebrations.

address: 004 P. Tavera St, San Fernando, La Union
description: Specializing in goat dishes like caldereta and papaitan, this is a go-to place for authentic Filipino flavors.

address: Copperleaf Street Capitol View Subdivision, San Fernando, 2500 La Union
description: A canteen-style restaurant offering affordable and home-cooked Filipino meals, perfect for a quick and satisfying bite.

address: San Juan, La Union
description: Makai Bowls is a popular spot in the coastal commune of San Juan, situated at the Great Northwest Philippine Travel Stop and Viewing Deck, offering stunning sea views. It was established to provide surfers and beach enthusiasts with a healthy dining option. Known for its dairy-free and sugar-free smoothie bowls made from 100% real fruits, Makai Bowls has relocated from Flotsam & Jetsam Hostel to its own place at the Travel Stop.

address: National Highway, San Juan, 2514 La Union
description: Sabong Fried Chicken is a cozy spot in the Great Northwest complex that's perfect for satisfying your fried chicken cravings. The menu is simple yet enticing, offering four types of chicken with four different sauces and a variety of sides. You can indulge in their Original Sabong Fried Chicken served with hand-cut fries and homemade banana ketchup, or try the kare-kare inspired version with honey-bagoong glaze, kare-kare sauce, and eggplant salsa.

address: M86F+PV2, MacArthur Hwy, San Juan, La Union
description: Flotsam & Jetsam Artist Beach Hostel is a popular beachfront accommodation in La Union, known for its relaxed atmosphere and vibrant crowd. The hostel offers modest dorms and private rooms, making it an ideal choice for travelers seeking a laid-back beach experience. In addition to providing surf lessons, the hostel features an eatery and bar where guests can socialize and enjoy the eclectic ambiance.

address: MacArthur Hwy, San Juan, 2514 La Union
description: If you're in San Juan and in need of a cozy spot to enjoy some coffee, Vietnamese cuisine, or comfort food, The Coffee Library is the place to be. It's a beloved spot in Elyu known for its delicious food and coffee at reasonable prices. With its convenient location near the beach and national highway, it's the perfect place to unwind and relax with good food and drinks.

address: Barangay, Costales st. Sitio Dappat, San Juan, 2514 La Union
description: Masa Bakehouse 2 has relocated to a larger, barn/warehouse-style space, offering a spacious and well-lit environment while maintaining the quality of their pastries and food. The crunchy kouign-amann is a standout, and the OG Beef Grilled Cheese provides a savory twist with its juicy beef pares filling. Despite potential peak time buzz, this La Union spot impresses with delicious food, relaxed atmosphere, and generous portions.

address: M85C+HWG, Urbiztondo Rd, San Juan, La Union
description: Located along Urbiztondo Road in San Juan La Union, BeachBum Food Park is a unique dining destination that offers a casual and laid-back atmosphere. It's not about luxury, but rather about enjoying outdoor dining, tasty food, and affordable beer. The park is particularly popular among visitors looking for a vibrant nightspot. Operating from Monday to Sunday with extended hours on weekends, it provides an ideal setting for socializing over delicious meals and drinks.

address: 134 Beachfront, MacArthur Highway,, Brgy. Urbiztondo, San Juan, 2514 La Union
description: Clean Beach Coffee is a charming restaurant located near MacArthur that offers delicious Balinese cuisine. One of their standout dishes is the bebek goreng, which is incredibly crispy and comes with a unique Chinese-style duck sauce. The restaurant takes pride in making everything in-house, including their flavorful sambal, noodles for bakso, and heavenly coconut ice cream. Clean Beach Coffee has convenient opening hours throughout the week, making it an ideal spot to satisfy your cravings for authentic Balinese flavors.

address: The Great Northwest Philippines Travel Stop and Viewing Deck, MacArthur Hwy, San Juan, La Union
description: Papa Bear is a cozy restaurant located in La Union, offering a diverse menu featuring Asian cuisine. The establishment takes pride in its themed dishes that showcase the flavors of Southeast Asian countries such as char kway teow, pho, and sambal pork. One of their signature offerings is the begg bowl, priced at just under two hundred pesos.

address: San Juan, La Union
description: Chu's Diner, a small Japanese restaurant located in the Great Northwest Food Park of San Juan, offers an authentic and delicious selection of Japanese cuisine. Run by Chu, a Japanese native now residing in San Juan, this cozy spot features a sushi bar as well as other traditional Japanese dishes. To ensure a seat at this popular eatery, it is recommended to arrive early as they have a cutoff time around 1:30 or 2 pm before resuming service at 5 pm.

address: F8WR+V5G, Bauang, La Union
description: Ciano Umok Gallery Cafe is a hidden gem located about 1km from the highway, offering a serene and relaxing atmosphere akin to a secret garden. The traditional architecture with modern touches adds to its charm. It's an ideal place to unwind, dine, and admire local artists' works displayed throughout the establishment. The cafe serves delicious food and beverages such as their signature coffee ti ay-ayo and Halo-Halo with distinct flavors.

address: MacArthur Hwy, San Juan, 2514 La Union
description: Little Canggu is a hidden gem in La Union, offering delicious and reasonably priced food with a nice ocean view. The ambiance is relaxing, making it a great spot to watch surfers while dining. The cafe also serves good nitro coffee at reasonable prices. It's pet-friendly and has friendly staff, clean facilities, and well-maintained surroundings. While the extended patio can be a bit wobbly, the overall experience of dining here is highly recommended.

address: M84C+GC4, Urbiztondo Rd, San Juan, La Union
description: Nestled along the main highway in La Union, Tipple and Brew Resto Bar is a charming haven for those seeking a laid-back drinking experience away from the bustling nightlife. This cozy gastropub specializes in an impressive selection of craft beers, including unique offerings from Engkanto Brewery and delightful flavored options like the vegan-friendly Peach Summer Ale. The menu features gourmet comfort food that pairs perfectly with your drink of choice, such as crispy onion rings and savory pork sisig.

address: M84C+V3Q, San Fernando, La Union
description: Seabuds in La Union offers a healthy and delicious breakfast with plant-based main dishes like tofu-based scrambled eggs, garlic brown rice, chopped tomatoes, and cucumber. The restaurant is known for its vegan-friendly options such as the Tapsilog Breakfast and Funky Monkey Smoothie Bowl. Despite the long waiting time during crowded weekends, visitors can enjoy their snacks by the beach at Seabuds' small covered dining area or rent mats and umbrellas near uncovered tables.

address: Pagudpod San Vicente Rd, San Fernando, La Union
description: Natalna Grille is a perfect place for dates, family gatherings and casual dining. It offers a wide range of menu with some must-try dishes such as grilled tuna belly and buttered mushroom with garlic. The view is nice since it overlooks the seashore while being quite and serene. The staff are friendly and accommodating making it a great choice for diners looking for an intimate atmosphere or convenient food without breaking the bank.

name_of_restaurant: Midway Grill & Restaurant - La Union's Best Kept Secret
address: MacArthur Hwy, San Fernando, La Union
description: Midway Grill & Restaurant is a hidden gem in La Union, offering delicious and affordable food that keeps customers coming back for more. The restaurant opens every day from 9:00 AM to 10:00 PM, making it convenient for locals and tourists alike. Customers rave about the generous portions and flavorful dishes such as baby back ribs, pancit guisado, sizzling pulpog, philly cheesesteak, beef brisket, Arroz a la Cubana, and more.

address: MacArthur Highway Brgy Carlatan Carlatan, San Fernando, 2524 La Union
description: Amare La Cucina in La Union is a must-visit for Italian food lovers. The restaurant offers the unique experience of making your own pizza from scratch. Their open kitchen with a stone oven allows you to witness the pizza-making process. The Grande 13 pizza is a popular choice, known for its generous size and delicious taste. Another recommended dish is the Wood Fire Ribs, which are tender, juicy, and served with honey glaze, fresh veggies, and rice.

address: 89G8+WHH, Agoo, La Union
description: Experience the taste of Ilocano cuisine at Makkan Ilocano Restaurant in Agoo, LA UNION! This place offers a wide selection of authentic dishes from the region, perfect for families, friends, and curious travelers. Indulge in their delicious bulalo, pakbet, pork sisig and adobong pusit sa gata. Don't forget to try their crispy dinuguan - one of their specialties!

address: Namboongan Barangay Road, Santo Tomas, 2505 La Union
description: If you're in the mood for Filipino cuisine, consider visiting Kambak Resto situated in Santo Tomas. This fine dining establishment offers a cozy atmosphere and serves up delicious and authentic ilokano dishes. The restaurant features a rustic native design, with a bungalow structure that can accommodate around 70 to 80 guests. It's an ideal place to stop by during a long drive heading north.

address: Curbside Villa, San Juan, La Union
description: Curo La Union is a picturesque dining spot that offers not only aesthetic appeal but also delectable food options. The menu caters to various cravings, from hearty breakfasts to vegan meals and beautifully presented pasta dishes. While the food preparation may take some time, the delicious offerings make it worth the wait. The ambiance is perfect for a dining experience, with attentive and warm servers adding to the overall pleasant atmosphere. It's advisable to make reservations in advance due to limited seating.

address: Bauang, La Union
description: The atmosphere at Denisia's Grill and Seafood Restaurant is pleasant, with live acoustic music adding to the ambiance. The food is reasonably priced and the portions are generous. While the bulalo was slightly sweet, the bagnet was incredibly crispy. The crispy dinuguan resembled fried meat dipped in dinuguan sauce. However, some customers preferred Gerry's Grill sisig over Denisia's version.

address: 183 2, 183 MacArthur Hwy, San Juan, 2514 La Union
description: Dampa sa San Juan is a restaurant that offers a delightful dining experience. The menu boasts a diverse array of dishes at affordable prices. Their seafood platter, which can easily satisfy a group of 4-5 people, is highly recommended. Patrons can expect freshly cooked meals, although there might be some waiting time during busy periods. The establishment provides ample parking space for vehicles and is ideal for groups and families. The staff are pleasant, accommodating, and friendly.

address: Town of Manaoag Zone, 6 Brgy. Lelemaan, Manaoag, 2430 Pangasinan
description: Hardin sa Paraiso Grill & Restaurant is a popular dining spot in Binalonan, Pangasinan, Philippines. It is known for its delicious Asian cuisine and seafood dishes. The restaurant offers a relaxing atmosphere where visitors can enjoy good food and hang out with friends or family. Located in a convenient area, it provides an ideal setting for travelers to indulge in local flavors and unwind after exploring the beautiful province of Pangasinan.

address: 28JG+M7J, De Venecia Hi-way Extension, Dagupan, 2400 Pangasinan
description: During your upcoming trip to Pangasinan, showcase breathtaking sights and delectable local cuisine on your social media feed. If you desire a place that offers both, Kainan ni Mang Peping eagerly awaits your arrival. This eatery captivates with its charming nipa huts and towering sculptures resembling popular cartoon characters and Marvel heroes. The establishment shares similarities with the inviting ambiance of Mang Inasal and exudes a distinct Filipino vibe that appeals to native guests.

address: DE VENECIA ROAD,EXTENTION,BRGY.PANTAL, DAGUPAN CITY,PANGASINAN, 2400 Pangasinan
description: Matutina's Gerry's Seafoods is a renowned restaurant in Dagupan, known for serving the best bangus in the Philippines. The restaurant is named after a character from the popular 80s sitcom John en Marsha. One of their must-try dishes is the Boneless Bangus Pinaputok. Located near the beach, it offers a great dining experience with delicious food to enjoy.

name_of_restaurant: Maxine By The Sea Seafood Restaurant
address: 52R4+92R, Alaminos - Lucap Rd, Alaminos, Pangasinan
description: Maxine By The Sea Seafood Restaurant is a laid-back dining spot with stunning sea views, located in Lucap, Alaminos City. Open every day from 7:00 AM to 10:00 PM, it offers a complimentary breakfast for guests staying at the nearby lodging. Visitors can enjoy good food while overlooking the beach, making it an ideal place to unwind after exploring Hundred Islands National Park.

address: 9V34+Q2W, Bolinao, Pangasinan
description: Sungayan Grill is a must-visit restaurant in Bolinao, known for its boodle fights featuring fresh seafood, best enjoyed during a river cruise along Balingasay River. The experience is reminiscent of the river tours in Loboc and Loay in Bohol. Families and groups of friends visiting Bolinao should not miss this unique dining experience.

address: 28MV+PJQ, Road, Dagupan, Pangasinan
description: Ciudad Elmina Fishing Village is a renowned restaurant in Pangasinan, offering a unique dining experience amidst colorful fishing boats and picturesque coastal views. The menu boasts an array of expertly prepared seafood dishes, showcasing the region's culinary heritage. Set in a traditional floating restaurant with nipa huts surrounded by fish ponds, it provides a relaxing ambiance for both locals and visitors. Known for its Dagupan-style food and seafood buffet, Ciudad Elmina is popular for celebrations and family gatherings.

address: 289J+P72, Gaudencio Siapno Rd, Dagupan, 2400 Pangasinan
description: Nestled along De Venecia Road in Dagupan City, Kuya Max is a beloved dining spot that draws in both families and young crowds with its affordable seafood offerings. This charming restogrill serves up local favorites like adobong talaba, spicy clam soup, and various preparations of the famous bangusÃÂwhether you prefer it sinuglaw, kilawin, steamed, or fried.

address: 29C5+M84, Dagupan, Pangasinan
description: DAGUPENA is a renowned restaurant in Dagupan City, offering a taste of the best flavors around Pangasinan Province. Known for its history and traditional dishes, it stands as one of the oldest restaurants in the city. Among its recommended specialties are papaitan and boneless bangus. The restaurant operates daily from 7 AM to 10 PM, inviting both locals and visitors to savor authentic Pangasinan cuisine.

address: Arellano St, Dagupan, Pangasinan
description: Silverio's Seafood Restaurant is a popular dining spot in Dagupan, offering a wide range of delicious seafood dishes. The restaurant boasts a relaxing ambiance with beautiful views of the river and bridge, making it an ideal place to unwind while enjoying a meal. Customers have praised the efficient and friendly staff, as well as the clean facilities. Additionally, visitors can look forward to live music performances starting at 7 pm on most nights, adding to the vibrant atmosphere.

address: Purok 3 Dagupan - Binmaley Rd, Dagupan, Pangasinan
description: When you enter Uson Pigar-Pigar Original, the delightful scent of grilled meats and spices envelops you, instantly creating a warm and inviting atmosphere. This charming eatery is celebrated for its authentic Filipino pigar-pigar, making it a must-visit spot in Dagupan. Locals often recommend Uson as the go-to place for this traditional dish, with many reminiscing about their cravings upon returning home from places like Manila or Baguio.

address: Zone 6, Bypass Road, Sitio Mitura Bridge, Urdaneta, 2428 Pangasinan
description: Nestled in the heart of Binalonan, Pangasinan, Cuisinero Garden Restaurant is a culinary gem that celebrates global flavors. The name itself hints at its mission to bring together diverse cuisines under one roof, making it a delightful destination for food enthusiasts. Diners can embark on a gastronomic journey with an extensive menu featuring Moroccan, Mediterranean, Chinese, American, and South American dishes.

address: 4XPV+XQG, Alaminos, Pangasinan
description: Eliana's Resto Grill offers a variety of traditional seafood dishes, including their popular sizzling seafood platter and mixed seafood specials. The menu also features tasty options like lemon chicken and ginulayang longganisa. Customers can enjoy their meals while surrounded by the serene ambiance of a rice paddy, with beautiful views of green fields extending towards the hills in the north. However, some improvements could be made to minimize noise from the nearby highway, such as adding bamboo buffers.

address: AB Fernandez E Ave, Dagupan, 2400 Pangasinan
description: Olivia's Pizzeria is a popular spot for pizza lovers, offering pick-up and delivery options. Their top dishes include nachos and pepperoni pizza. While some customers have had disappointing experiences with broken glassware and cleanliness issues in the past, others have praised the excellent service and great food, particularly recommending the truffle pasta, 12" pizza, and chicken wings meal set. The restaurant is known for its generous servings and superb service in a cozy atmosphere.

address: 28MJ+G8F, Dagupan, 2400 Pangasinan
description: Chef Distrito is a restaurant that offers Filipino and Asian cuisine, featuring dishes like bagnet kare-kare. They also have a selection of cakes and pastries. The venue has a simple ambiance, with some mentioning it resembling a hospital canteen. Despite this, the food is highly praised for its taste and value for money. Some recommended dishes include the bagnet kare-kare rice meal and seafood kare-kare.

name_of_restaurant: Dampa Sa Pangasinan - Seafood's Restaurant and Catering Services
address: Purok 4 Nancayasan, MacArthur Hwy, Urdaneta, 2428 Pangasinan
description: If you ask anyone for a great seafood place in the metro, Dampa Sa Pangasinan - Seafood's Restaurant and Catering Services would likely be the top suggestion. This restaurant offers a unique experience where customers can choose their own seafood from a wet market and have it prepared to their liking. It is an ideal location for family gatherings with its spacious setting. However, there may be some waiting time during busy periods such as peak hours or special events like graduations or Valentine's Day.

address: Royal Rays Food Hall, Jose De Venencia Extension, Pantal Rd, Barangay Pantal, Dagupan, 2400 Pangasinan
description: Juliana's Kitchen is the ultimate destination for an adventure into Asian cuisine. They specialize in a diverse range of dishes from Thailand, Malaysia-Singapore, and Vietnam, making it a go-to place for all your Asian food cravings. Located in Dagupan, it offers an unrivaled selection of authentic delicacies that are hard to find elsewhere in the area.

address: Binmaley, Pangasinan, Binmaley, 2417 Pangasinan
description: At first, there was some apprehension due to the absence of a menu and prices; customers had to personally select their desired dishes. The restaurant offered a variety of options including stir-fry vegetables, inasal, caldereta, and their renowned huge crab priced at 500 pesos each. Despite initial concerns, the final bill came to approximately 1200 pesos with the inclusion of rice and drinks, which was deemed reasonable.

address: 289P+2W9, Judge Jose de Venecia Ave, Dagupan, Pangasinan
description: Panaderia Antonio Bakery & Restaurant is a well-known establishment in Dagupan, offering a variety of freshly baked breads and healthy food options. It is the home of Plato Wraps and has been serving the community for over 10 years. The menu includes pizza, burgers, pasta, Kare-Kare, and more. Despite its popularity, the restaurant maintains a humble atmosphere with available parking slots. The staff is accommodating and has adapted well to changes during the Covid-19 pandemic.

address: Tondaligan Rd, Bonuan, Dagupan, Pangasinan
description: The Original Matutina's Restaurant offers a warm and inviting ambiance with rustic decor and traditional Filipino touches, creating a nostalgic dining experience. The restaurant prides itself on hospitality, ensuring a memorable visit for diners. Known for its traditional Filipino cuisine, the restaurant features popular dishes using fresh produce from Pangasinan, including Bangus (milk fish), shrimps, crabs, oysters, and vegetables.

address: 5GC9+F9H, MacArthur Hwy, Sison, Pangasinan
description: Leeza's Restaurant is a convenient stop located near the Pozzorubio exit at TPLEX, making it easily accessible for travelers. This 24-hour restaurant welcomes large groups without prior reservations and offers ample parking space. The menu features home-cooked local dishes, including their renowned papaitan, and also includes pasalubong items for purchase. While some find the prices slightly higher than expected, others appreciate the variety of menu options available.

address: 289Q+CXX, Judge Jose de Venecia Ave, Dagupan, Pangasinan
description: Jech's Bakery & Restaurant is a popular dining spot located in Calasiao, Pangasinan, near Dagupan City. It offers a wide variety of tasty dishes and baked goods. The restaurant is well-established with clean facilities and reasonable prices. While some visitors found the noise level to be high, many praised the delicious food and generous portions.

name_of_restaurant: Kainan Sa Kubo Ningnangan Ed Manaoag
address: 85 Caloocan, Manaoag, 2430 Pangasinan
description: Kainan Sa Kubo Ningnangan Ed Manaoag offers a delightful dining experience with delicious food options like Sinigang na hipon, dinakdakan, grilled bangus, bulalo, and leche flan. The place is spacious with the choice of dining in an airconditioned kubo or a traditional one without AC. Despite some items not being available on the menu and cleanliness issues in the comfort rooms, visitors appreciate the early arrival to avoid crowds after attending mass at Manaoag Church. The staff is accommodating, and overall service is excellent according to reviewers.

name_of_restaurant: Acl Iloilo's Authentic La Paz Batchoy Food House
address: Dagupan - Binmaley Rd, Binmaley, Pangasinan
description: ACL Iloilo's Authentic La Paz Batchoy Food House is a new restaurant in town that offers a variety of delicious and affordable meals. Their specialty includes authentic La Paz Batchoy, sizzling scallops, pigar, and kaleskes. The restaurant is known for its clean environment and friendly staff. It's the perfect place to enjoy Iloilo cuisine with friends while trying out their signature dishes like sizzling scallops.

address: 26QP+2V5, Baywalk, Lingayen, Pangasinan
description: Nestled in the vibrant culinary scene of Pangasinan, Philippines, Chatanoga Grill Seafoods & Restaurant offers a warm and inviting atmosphere for both locals and tourists. Conveniently located at Baywalk, Lingayen, the restaurant is known for its tasty dishes like sisig and panga sinigang served with rice. With reliable parking and friendly staff, it's a great spot to enjoy delicious seafood while being entertained by live music and dance performances.

address: Bonjour, Tapuac District, Dagupan City, Pangasinan
description: Camp Pares DGP has quickly become a popular spot in Dagupan City, drawing crowds eager to savor its renowned pares. Locals particularly appreciate the reasonable prices and the delicious food, making it a hit among residents and visitors alike. The establishment is known for its warm hospitality and satisfying dining experience, making it a must-visit destination for those seeking authentic local cuisine.

name_of_restaurant: CIAO Pizzeria By The Sea & Mezze Club
address: Sundowners Marina, Bolinao, 2406 Pangasinan
description: Experience the pleasure of live acoustic performances while enjoying cocktails with your companions at Ciao Pizzeria By The Sea. Indulge in their renowned sizzling shrimp, a must-try dish. Their Facebook Page provides information and their contact number is 0921 913 8780. Situated in Sundowners Marina, Bolinao, Pangasinan, the restaurant offers a perfect ambience and a relaxing view.

address: 1 Long Beach Street, Barangay Arnedo, Bolinao, 2409 Pangasinan
description: Nestled in the charming Barangay Arnedo, The Blue Mikey is a newly opened gem that might require a bit of navigation to find. Just follow the Birdland resort signs along Patar Road and take a right at the elementary school; soon enough, you'll arrive at this delightful eatery after winding through scenic turns. Once you step inside, you're greeted by a relaxed atmosphere perfect for unwinding after exploring nearby Long Beach or Patar Beach.

name_of_restaurant: Giant Taklobo Seafood and Grill Ilog Malino Branch
address: Patar Rd, Bolinao, 2406 Pangasinan
description: Experience delectable freshly caught seafood at the renowned Giant Taklobo Seafood and Grill. Situated just a short distance from various caves and waterfalls, this restaurant guarantees a memorable dining experience. With an extensive menu offering bilao packages suitable for the entire family, guests can indulge in their favorite seafood dishes in an open-air setting reminiscent of a traditional bahay kubo.

address: 229 Perez Blvd, Downtown District, Dagupan, 2400 Pangasinan
description: Silantro Fil-Mex Cantina is a restaurant that combines Mexican flavors with a Filipino twist. Their popular menu items include beef nachos and caliente wings. For heartier options, they offer Silantros burrito, lamb-chop, and grilled mahi-mahi. The restaurant has gained a reputation since its introduction in 2016 and is a reliable choice for those seeking to please friends with different food preferences.

address: Lenox Hotel, Rizal St, Downtown District, Dagupan, 2400 Pangasinan
description: CafÃÂ© Feliz provides a cozy dining atmosphere where guests can enjoy freshly brewed Italian coffee accompanied by mouthwatering desserts. The restaurant also features KTV rooms suitable for groups of all sizes, making it an ideal venue for social gatherings and special occasions.

address: 9R48+C7V, Bolinao, Pangasinan
description: Mangunguna Seafood Bar and Grill is a great dining option for those looking to avoid the typical resort food found at larger resorts nearby. Situated near Patar Beach, it offers a convenient stop to enjoy a delicious ocean-to-table experience with freshly caught seafood. The restaurant's friendly and efficient service, along with its rustic-style structures, create a welcoming atmosphere for guests.

address: 5HQH+343, Laoag - Paoay Rd, Laoag City, Ilocos Norte
description: Snacksbest Ilocos Miki and Empanada are popular afternoon snacks in Ilocos Norte and Ilocos Sur. The empanada is a bright orange half-moon-shaped pastry filled with Ilocos longganisa, eggs, green papaya, and parboiled mung beans. Despite the overwhelming number of customers, the food is delicious and satisfying for Filipino taste buds.

address: 4HHH+JXM, San Nicolas, Ilocos Norte
description: Jesmine's Eatery Bagnet Special is a beloved dish featuring deep-fried crispy pork cracklings, best enjoyed with a side of bagoong and calamansi sauce. This flavorful delight pairs perfectly with the classic Pinakbet, a traditional Filipino meat stew served with boiled vegetables and shrimp paste. It's an ideal choice for those looking to savor authentic Filipino cuisine. The restaurant also offers excellent service, making it a great dining option for both locals and visitors alike.

address: Arabella's Events Place, F. Julian, Laoag City, Ilocos Norte
description: La Preciosa Ilocos Corp is a renowned culinary destination in Laoag City, known for serving the best carrot cake in Ilocos. The restaurant has humble beginnings, originating from a small kitchenette managed by Preciosa Palma, the mother of the restaurant owner.

address: Paseo de Paoay, 2nd Floor, Brgy. 18 Veronica, Paoay, 2902 Ilocos Norte
description: Smoke Bar and Restaurant is a great place to get delicious food in Ilocos Norte. The restaurant has a nice structure, good ventilation, well-spaced seats, and excellent service. They have smoked beef that is very tender and their salmon in Creamy Lemon Butter is awesome! Their mashed potatoes are also really good.

address: Ilocos Norte, Hernando, Lungsod ng Laoag
description: Cuisine de Iloco Restaurant in Laoag City offers a diverse menu of classic Filipino dishes, including hearty soups, flavorful seafood specialties, and traditional vegetable stews like Pinakbet and Dinengdeng. The restaurant is popular with both locals and tourists due to its cozy interior, friendly service, and delicious food. It's a must-visit spot that provides a cultural lesson for your palate.

address: Brgy. 40, Bacarra, 2916 Ilocos Norte
description: Located in the charming town of Bacarra, PLANAXIS Grill and Restaurant offers a diverse menu to cater to various tastes. Open from 10:00 AM to 9:00 PM, this gem boasts a welcoming ambiance and spacious parking and dining areas. The restaurant provides a homey dining experience with attentive staff. Guests recommend trying their Bagnet, Sinigang, and Kare-Kare dishes.

address: 3H37+7MV, Brgy. 1 S Valdez, Batac, 2906 Ilocos Norte
description: Batac Riverside Empanadaan is a popular spot known for serving arguably the best empanadas in Ilocos. The empanadas, available at stalls like Lanies or Glorys, are filled with indigenous longaniza and papaya flavors, creating a burst of deliciousness. Visitors often return for more of these satisfying snacks. In addition to the famous empanadas, the food court offers other local culinary delights such as longganisa, dried squid, and pilais.

address: 29 Gen. Segundo Ave, Laoag City, 2900 Ilocos Norte
description: Eagles' Nest Bar and Restaurant, located in Laoag City, is a must-visit dining spot known for its skillfully crafted signature dishes. The Bagnet, a crispy pork belly delicacy served with tangy vinegar dipping sauce, and the Empanada filled with a savory mixture of ground meat and vegetables are crowd favorites. The restaurant offers an inviting ambiance amidst lush greenery and breathtaking views, providing the perfect setting for a relaxing meal.

address: Cleveland, Brgy. 2, San Nicolas, 2901 Ilocos Norte
description: Ladrillos Restaurant, located in San Nicolas, offers a modern twist on traditional Ilocano dishes. The extensive menu caters to all tastes and is available from 10:00 AM to 9:00 PM. The restaurant provides a remarkable dining experience with an ambiance that exudes beauty and warmth, making visitors feel at home. Additionally, the restaurant features a sizable museum on the side, adding to its appeal.

address: 3, Sitio Bangbanga - Purok Laud, Badoc, Ilocos Norte
description: Inuwayan Winery in Adams offers a unique experience with its fruit wines, distinct from traditional grape wines. The winery boasts an international quality of wine at affordable prices, featuring a wide variety of red wines and even champagne. Visitors can enjoy sweet and medium dry wines while learning about the wine-making process through generous sampling and educational sessions. The accessible location makes it convenient for all guests to explore the diverse range of fruit wines offered by this family-owned establishment.

address: 5HWV+PV3, Segunda Ave. & Cor. M.H. Del Pilar, Brgy. 13, Laoag City, 2900 Ilocos Norte
description: If you're searching for a spot in Laoag City with a nostalgic American atmosphere to enjoy lunch, snacks, or dinner, Macy's Diner is the place for you. This eatery exudes a retro ambiance that appeals to lovers of all things vintage. While some customers wish they would enhance their snack options, others appreciate the delectable tapsilog breakfast served with sukang iloko vinegar.

address: Barangay Road, Pagudpud, 2919 Ilocos Norte
description: Emohruo Beach Restobar is a beachfront dining spot that offers stunning ocean views and a refreshing breeze. The tropical burger, made from scratch and served with fresh fruit, is highly recommended. While the lack of air conditioning may be a downside for some, the ambiance and view make up for it. Guests can enjoy delicious dishes like dinakdakan and cocktails while listening to the soothing sound of waves crashing on the shore.

name_of_restaurant: Fremantle Pizzeria Al Fresco Dining Laoag
address: Brgy 40 Sitio Salladay, Balatong, Laoag City, 2900 Ilocos Norte
description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Laoag, Fremantle Pizzeria offers a delightful dining experience that combines an inviting atmosphere with exceptional hospitality. This charming eatery is easily accessible for both locals and tourists, making it a perfect stop for anyone craving delicious food. As you enter, the mouthwatering scent of freshly baked pizzas fills the air, setting the stage for a memorable meal.

address: Laoag City, Ilocos Norte
description: Kamalig Garden Grill & Restaurant is a great spot to savor Ilocano cuisine while being entertained by live music and enjoying your favorite drinks. The restaurant features a two-floor dining area with traditional wooden interiors, Nipa hut roofs, and an open space for live band performances. They offer delicious Bilao meals perfect for sharing with a group. The place can get crowded, and parking is limited, but once inside, the spacious interior provides a family-friendly atmosphere.

address: GM9Q+MW, Bangui, 2920 Ilocos Norte
description: Located along the national highway, 18ÃÂ° North Camping Cafe and Diner is a hidden gem offering a charming ambiance and breathtaking views of the Bangui windmills and Pagudpud beach. The cafe serves top-notch coffee drinks at reasonable prices, while the food is described as rich and delightful. Visitors can enjoy their meals outside to take in the stunning scenery. Additionally, the cafe provides a unique camping area for outdoor enthusiasts.

address: 3G6C+R3V, Herencia Plaza, McArthur Street corner Marcos Avenue, Paoay, 2902 Ilocos Norte
description: Don Empanada is a snack bar located near several restaurants in Vigan. They specialize in Vigan-style empanadas, which have an orange crust filled with papaya and egg. The prices have recently increased to 60 P per empanada. Despite being a small outdoor kiosk, it offers inexpensive and freshly cooked food that is served quickly.

address: 3G6C+R3J, Herencia Plaza, McArthur Street corner Marcos Avenue, Paoay, 2902 Ilocos Norte
description: Ilocos Coolers is a popular refreshment stand located across from the historic Paoay Church in Paoay, Ilocos Norte, Philippines. They are renowned for their award-winning halo-halo, a traditional Filipino dessert featuring a mix of sweetened fruits, jellies, and beans, topped with shaved ice, milk, and often ice cream.

address: 4G9G+MM6, Paoay, Ilocos Norte
description: Jowtoo Natural Cuisine is a Japanese restaurant located in Paoay, Ilocos Norte, Philippines. They specialize in Japanese dishes such as sushi, sashimi, ramen, and okonomiyaki, as well as steak.

address: 3G5M+QG3, Marcos Ave, Paoay, 2902 Ilocos Norte
description: Najian Pojangmacha & Samgyeopsal is a Korean restaurant located in Paoay, Ilocos Norte, Philippines. They specialize in Samgyeopsal, a popular Korean dish featuring grilled pork belly, and offer an unlimited Samgyeopsal experience.

address: Arabella Events Place, Brgy. 2 F. Julian Street along pila road) Laoag City, Ilocos Norte (Beside, Laoag City, 2900 Ilocos Norte
description: Fika Street Cafe is a cozy cafÃÂ© located in Laoag City, Ilocos Norte, Philippines. They offer a variety of coffee beverages and light snacks, providing a comfortable space for relaxation and socializing.

address: Gov. Primo Lazaro, Laoag City, 2900 Ilocos Norte
description: Laoag Lomi House - Banga Banga is a restaurant that serves delectable dishes in a pleasant ambiance. The eatery offers a wide array of flavorful meals, ranging from traditional Filipino cuisine to international favorites. Patrons can enjoy their culinary creations in a cozy and inviting setting, providing an enjoyable dining experience. This establishment prides itself on its diverse menu selection, ensuring there is something for every palate.

address: 1 Crisologo, Brgy 2, Vigan City, 2700 Ilocos Sur
description: Cafe Leona is a restaurant located in Vigan, known for its historical significance and diverse menu. Situated near the Leona Florentino statue and marker, it offers a variety of food options at reasonable prices. Despite the tight and fusty setting, the cafe's menu reflects a commitment to diversity. The downstairs restaurant serves good food and espresso, making it a convenient dining option for visitors exploring the area.

address: 1 Bonifacio, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: Kusina Felicitas is a restaurant located in Grandpas Inn, offering an 18th-century ambiance with brick walls and historical art, creating a nostalgic feel of dining during the Hispanic era. The rustic handcrafted wooden furniture adds to the historical charm. Specializing in traditional Ilocano and Filipino food, Kusina Felicitas is known for its Vigan specialties such as pipian and grilled chicken with tropical karimbuaya leaves.

address: Hotel, Plaza Burgos, Vigan Plaza, Crisologo, Vigan City, 2077 Lalawigan ng Ilocos Sur
description: Cafe Bigaa is a charming restaurant located in Vigan City, Ilocos Sur, offering a delightful fusion of flavors with genuine Ilocano ingredients. Situated at the heart of Florentino and Plaridel streets, this establishment is known for its authentic Spanish dish turned Filipino, the Paella Ilocandia. Originally a gastropub, Cafe Bigaa has evolved into a restaurant specializing in local Ilocano fusion dishes.

address: Grandpa's Inn, 1 Bonifacio, Vigan City, Lalawigan ng Ilocos Sur
description: Cafe Uno in Vigan is a popular spot known for its cozy ambiance, making it perfect for intimate dates and late-night conversations. This cafe is renowned for its delectable cakes, pasta, and a variety of silog meals that are favored by tourists for breakfast. Additionally, Cafe Uno offers local dishes such as kare-kare and bagnet sisig.

address: 14 Crisologo, Vigan City, 2700 Ilocos Sur
description: Nestled in the historic Vigan City, 1995 Studio Cafe is a modern restaurant and cafe that offers a fusion of local Ilocano dishes and Western favorites. Located near the iconic Calle Crisologo, this popular spot is known for its delicious pizza, chicken wings with a local twist, calzone, and filling rice meals. The cafe also serves an array of beverages including coffees, teas, smoothies as well as delectable cakes.

address: H9CQ+GRW, Salcedo, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: When exploring the charming streets of Vigan, one cannot miss the delightful experience of indulging in Irene's Vigan Empanada. This beloved eatery has become a staple for both locals and visitors, offering a unique twist on the traditional Ilocano empanada. Unlike its Spanish counterpart, which is typically baked, this local version is fried to perfection, creating a crispy exterior that perfectly complements its flavorful filling.

address: corner Crisologo, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: BarTech is a well-lit restaurant located along the historic Calle Crisologo in Vigan, offering live acoustic music and renowned as the first and only evening buffet in the area. The name "BarTech" is derived from the Ilocano word "bartek," meaning to be inebriated.

address: H968+534, Hidden Garden, Barangay Bulala, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur, Vigan City
description: Lilong & Lilang Coffee Shop is a charming restaurant located amidst lush gardens and a nature trail. The thatched-roof and plant-filled interior create a cozy atmosphere for enjoying authentic Ilocano dishes. Visitors can also indulge in refreshing bubble teas like the popular Kiwi Milk Tea, making it a favorite spot for locals and tourists alike. With its picturesque location, quality service, and delicious food, this coffee shop offers an unforgettable dining experience in the heart of Hidden Gardens.

address: H9HJ+53C, Burgos St, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: Angkong Seafood Restaurant is a popular dining spot in Vigan, known for serving authentic Chinese cuisine in the heart of Ilocos Sur. The restaurant offers a wide range of affordable dishes that cater to both locals and tourists, making it an ideal choice for those looking to experience genuine Chinese flavors while exploring the historic city. With its rich culinary heritage influenced by both Spanish and Chinese cultures, Vigan provides a unique backdrop for enjoying traditional and fusion cuisines.

address: H9CQ+7JJ, Mabini, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: Casa Jardin Empanada & Okoy, also known as CJs, has evolved from a modest carinderia to become one of Vigan's most popular dining spots. This cozy restaurant nestled in a lush garden is celebrated for its generous portions of empanada and okoy.

address: Salcedo, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: Coffee Break Vigan is a cozy cafÃÂ© located along Calle Crisologo at Salcedo Street intersection, making it a convenient spot for a refreshing drink or hot coffee while exploring Vigan. The cafÃÂ© offers the award-winning Sigay Robusta coffee and an array of affordable espresso-based drinks. In addition to beverages, they also serve budget-friendly rice meals, snacks, and pasta.

address: G9WJ+V9W, Caoayan, Ilocos Sur
description: Ihawan sa Caoayan started as a small food cart and has now become a renowned grilled restaurant in Ilocos Sur. The dining area, made of nipa huts, offers customers a traditional Filipino kamayan experience. They serve delicious local and seafood dishes and have a well-designed mess hall layout with a pleasant atmosphere. The staff is extremely polite, although it is not a fast-food establishment so patience is required.

address: H9FM+PXH, Bonifacio, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: GaizelÃÂs Carinderia is a popular dining spot located near Gen. Luna Street and Florentino Street in Vigan. It's known for its extensive menu of Ilocano dishes served buffet-style, with a focus on delicious vegetable dishes like dinengdeng. The carinderia offers authentic Ilocano cuisine such as warek warek, igado, lomo lomo, sinanglao, and more.

address: Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: TongsonÃÂs Royal Bibingka is a must-visit spot near Plaza Burgos in Vigan, offering delicious longganisa by kilos or dozens. It's a popular destination for locals and tourists alike. In addition to their famous bibingka, TongsonÃÂs also offers other Ilocos snacks like tinubong and canutillos.

address: Crisologo, Encarnacion, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: Cafe Evelyn, situated at the Casa Blanca Hotel, is a charming restaurant that serves a blend of modern and traditional Ilocano and western dishes. The menu features an array of options, including authentic Ilocano cuisine as well as fusion dishes that incorporate elements from other culinary traditions. Notable offerings include the popular Vigan longganisa.

address: Saint Paul Avenue, Bantay, Ilocos Sur
description: Ikan Dampa is a seafood eatery situated on the Boardwalk Fuerte Beach in Caoayan, just outside of Vigan City Proper. Utilizing Waze can help you find this establishment easily. The cuisine offered here is delightful, and the restaurant boasts a pleasant view. However, one drawback is that their menu mainly caters to larger groups, making it challenging for smaller parties to order dishes according to their preferences due to the requirement of ordering substantial portions.

name_of_restaurant: PANGANAN KEN IHAWAN TOY CIUDAD TI VIGAN
address: H9FM+PXP, Bonifacio, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: Panganan Ken Ihawan Toy Ciudad ti Vigan, also known as Restaurant and Grill in the City of Vigan, is a popular eatery offering Filipino and Ilocano vegetable and meat dishes. It is a cafeteria-style restaurant where diners line up with trays to choose their meals. The place can get crowded during peak hours, attracting both locals and tourists seeking authentic Ilocano cuisine at affordable prices.

address: 5CRX+RQH, CariÃÂ±o Street, Candon, Ilocos Sur
description: Located in the heart of Candon Ilocos, Inapuyan Restaurant embodies the essence of homestyle cooking. Housed in a converted residence, this eatery boasts ample air conditioning units to provide relief from the scorching outdoor temperatures. The cuisine is exceptional, showcasing meticulous preparation infused with love and passion. The friendly staff warmly welcomes guests and attends to their every need, ensuring a delightful dining experience. Inapuyan Restaurant leaves patrons eager to return for more savory delights.

address: 16 A Bonifacio, Vigan City, 2700 Ilocos Sur
description: Sanitary Restaurant Branch 1, situated in Ilocos Sur, Philippines, is a popular dining spot known for its clean and hygienic environment. The restaurant offers a diverse menu featuring traditional Filipino dishes and international cuisines to cater to various tastes. Visitors can enjoy local favorites such as lomi, mami, pancit Luzon, siopao, and siomai in this bustling Chinese-Ilokano restaurant.

address: Candon Diversion Rd, Vigan City, 2700 Ilocos Sur
description: Kardo's Grill House is a cozy restaurant situated in the scenic province of Ilocos Sur, Philippines. It is well-known for its delectable grilled dishes that highlight the rich flavors of Filipino cuisine. The restaurant offers a delightful dining experience with friendly service and a warm ambiance. While some patrons have noted small serving sizes, others have praised the seafood boodle fight and the variety of options available for their unli grill offering.

address: H9FP+4M5, Vigan City, Ilocos Sur
description: Tessie's Restaurant in Vigan is a popular choice for budget-conscious travelers looking for satisfying meals. This two-storey carinderia-style eatery offers a variety of affordable dishes, including silog and budget meals priced between 50 to 150. Visitors rave about the huge, tasty siopao and the lomi dish with kimchi. While some find the siopao okay but slightly dry, others appreciate its soft and tasty bun.

address: HCQ8+Q55, MABILBILASUR CITY &, Bantay, CITY, Bantay, Ilocos Sur
description: The restaurant Mira Hills is a good stop for traveller going to Vigan or Ilocos Norte. The food is good and the price is reasonable. It even has a pasalubong center. The vigan longanisa are vacuum packed and frozen; the restaurant also have outdoor seating. Notice a small stage.

address: Patpata Access Road, Candon, 2710 Ilocos Sur
description: Inong's Yard Restaurant & Cafe is a charming and picturesque establishment, offering a warm and inviting atmosphere. Patrons can enjoy a delectable selection of dishes, with the beef samgyupsal being one of the notable options on the menu. However, it would be enhanced if there were various flavors offered for the different cuts available. The restaurant prides itself on delivering top-notch services and maintaining high-quality standards in both their cuisine and customer experience.

address: HCJX+FVR, Bantay, Ilocos Sur
description: Senorita Dulce House of Foods is a roadside eatery that attracts travelers seeking a break, whether for refreshment, nourishment, or relaxation. The total payment for three dishes, inclusive of rice and water, amounted to 455 pesos. While the portion sizes were disappointingly small and the dinakdakan was slightly tough, the sinigang na bangus stood out with its excellent taste. The establishment's decor is decent and cleanliness deserves praise.

address: Metro, Encarnacion Cpd, Bayubay Sur, San Vicente, Vigan City, 2726 Ilocos Sur
description: Govantes Bistro & Guesthouse is a charming riverside restaurant and guesthouse in Vigan. The bistro offers an excellent selection of food, including Stuffed Squid and Pinakbet with Bagnet. The well-ventilated restaurant has electric fans for added comfort. It accepts GCash and credit cards as modes of payment. Guests praise the relaxed ambiance, friendly staff, and beautiful riverside view.

address: 6CMM+R4F, Rosario, La Union
description: Sagat Crust Food House is a charming old house turned into a food haven located along the national highway in Amlang, Rosario, La Union. The menu boasts an array of delectable treats such as Carabao Burger, scalded Carabao Milk, Empanada and the highly recommended Beef Mushroom pizza.

address: Brgy, San Juan, 2514 La Union
description: Waves Point Resto Bar is a newly opened Peruvian beachfront dining spot located along the popular surf strip of San Juan. The restaurant offers a unique blend of Spanish, Chinese, and Japanese flavors with an island vibe. Situated in front of the Mebuyans Vessell art installation, the spacious venue provides ample parking and a refreshing ocean breeze. While the decor may be aging and the music lacks effort, it offers unobstructed views and delicious cuisine.

address: San Juan, La Union
description: Bay-Bay Seafood & Grill, a popular seafood eatery situated in San Juan within the Ciabel Hotel premises, is renowned for its delectable array of oceanic offerings. Diners can indulge in their well-known Ultimate Seafood Feast, a generous platter of marine delicacies accompanied by unlimited servings of rice and meant to be enjoyed boodle fight style. The cuisine at Bay-Bay Seafood & Grill is highly regarded for its scrumptious flavors and appropriately portioned servings.

address: San Fernando, La Union
description: Seawadeeka is a restaurant that specializes in serving Asian staples such as pad Thai, nasi lemak, and satay. It started as a food truck before establishing a permanent location in Urbiztondo. The restaurant is known for its affordable Asian street food offerings like Pork Satay Sticks, Pad Thai, and Vietnamese Fresh Spring Rolls.

address: 24 208, Agoo, La Union
description: Lakay Ago Nature's Park in Agoo is a charming nature park with a hobbit-inspired nook and an open-air restaurant nestled in a picturesque garden setting. The park boasts an array of Bougainvillea, the provincial flower of La Union, and offers stunning sunset views over the town. It also provides camping grounds and serves as a venue for various special events.

address: Great Northwest Philippines Travel Stop and View Deck, MacArthur Hwy, San Juan, 2513 La Union
description: Coco Mama La Union is a popular dessert spot known for its dairy-free and vegan coconut ice cream served in a coconut husk. The delicately balanced, not overly sweet ice cream is topped with pinipig for a crunchy contrast. With its second branch in San Juan after the success of its Boracay location, both locals and tourists love their unique ice cream offerings. In addition to the delicious coconut ice cream, they also serve buko pandan flavor and offer mochi balls.

address: M84C+JH2, San Fernando, La Union
description: Silong CafÃÂ© offers a variety of breakfast meals, with the option to order additional servings for those with bigger appetites. The staff is friendly and the cafÃÂ© is open 24/7, making it convenient for any time of day. The affordable prices make it a great spot for a filling meal, and they also offer fruit shakes at reasonable prices. Customers appreciate the delicious food and the free-flowing soup that comes with their meals.
